# Spec 015 — Pin Address & Panel Polish

Status: Draft
Owner: <you>
Related: 010 (geocode endpoint family, panel layout), 004 (hardening
invariants for the new endpoint), 005 (mobile sheets), 014 (the Afford.
button this fixes)

## Overview

Four contained quality fixes. The work pin gains a live "nearest address"
label via reverse geocoding (the informative replacement for the static
label removed in the 010 polish). The budget input formats with thousands
separators and the left panel adopts a consistent type scale. The metric
switcher stops truncating "Afford." by becoming a 2×2 grid. And on phones,
both bottom sheets collapse to slim handles so the map can own the screen.

## Requirements

- **R1 — Reverse-geocoded pin address.** `GET /api/geocode/reverse?lat&lon`
  resolves the nearest address via Mapbox (same family as forward
  geocoding), with the full 004 hardening: input snapped to the 500 m grid
  BEFORE cache key and upstream call, 24 h cache including misses, budget
  reserve(1), per-IP rate limit, coverage geofence (422 — this endpoint is
  not a free worldwide reverse geocoder), no-token/budget/upstream → 503,
  no match → 404. The work section displays the address under the search
  box, debounced against pin drags, best-effort (absent on failure); a
  forward-search result seeds the label instantly without a round trip.
- **R2 — Budget formatting.** The budget input displays thousands
  separators while typing ("800,000") and still emits the parsed number;
  pasting formatted values works.
- **R3 — Type scale.** Panel font sizes consolidate onto three tokens
  (section 12px / control 13px / hint 11px) applied across all panel
  sections, ending the per-component drift.
- **R4 — Metric-switcher fitment.** The four metric buttons render as a
  2×2 grid: every label fully legible at the panel's width, with headroom
  for a future fifth metric. Tap targets stay ≥40 px.
- **R5 — Mobile sheet collapse.** On ≤768 px viewports, the controls sheet
  and the ZIP-detail sheet each collapse to a slim handle (≈56 px) via a
  keyboard-accessible toggle with `aria-expanded`; tapping re-expands.
  Selecting a new ZIP re-expands the detail sheet. Desktop is unaffected.

## Non-functional / Constraints

- Reverse geocode cost: 1 upstream call per snapped pin cell per 24 h
  (~250 m label imprecision from the snap is accepted).
- No new dependencies. Token safety (001 R5) unchanged.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Dragging the pin updates the address line after settling; address
      search shows its label instantly; no-token mode shows no line.
- [ ] Two pin positions <500 m apart produce one upstream reverse call.
- [ ] Budget shows separators while typing and round-trips parsed values.
- [ ] "Affordability" button text is fully visible; all four metrics
      reachable; keyboard focus ring intact.
- [ ] At 390 px: both sheets collapse to handles showing the full map and
      re-expand on tap; new ZIP selection re-expands the detail sheet.
- [ ] `pytest` and `npm run test` green with the new endpoint, hook,
      format, switcher, and collapse tests.

## Out of Scope (explicit)

- Reverse geocoding for arbitrary map clicks (work pins only).
- Caret-position preservation in the budget input (end-caret accepted).

